You are here: SALESFORCE HELP DOCS ANALYTICS Hiding a Report Chart That Shows an Error

A chart can sometimes show an error on the detail page instead of data. You have the option to hide it from viewers.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
Available in: Enhanced Folder Sharing

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
Enhanced Folder Sharing
Create and Customize Reports
Report Builder

To hide such a chart, select Hide chart with error from the Chart Properties dialog box.

A chart can show an error for one or more of these reasons:
The viewer doesn’t have access to the field that’s used for filtering.
The viewer doesn’t have access to the report folder.
The report chart has been deleted from the report.
The report definition has changed.
The report itself is no longer available.
title: Hiding Error Report Charts in Salesforce
